<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Addison Rae was named the highest-earning TikTok personality in Forbes' first-ever list, raking in over $5 million in one calendar year ending in June 2020.</p>

<p>With endorsements and a role in the upcoming remake of the late 90s classic She's All That on the horizon, the Louisiana native made a pitstop for a workout at the Dogpound gym in West Hollywood on Thursday.</p>

<p>The 19-year-old emerged from the facility with a couple of friends looking fit and ready, all while wearing a protective mask amid the still ongoing COVID-19 pandemic.</p>

<p>Rock solid: Addison Rae showed off her fit figure after a workout in Los Angeles on Thursday</p>

<p>Rae showed off her curves in a sporty ensemble that consisted of black leggings and a matching sports bra.</p>

<p>She also donned white sneakers and had a white sweatshirt tied over her right shoulder.</p>

<p>The dancer pulled her dark brown tresses back into a loose ponytail. </p>

<p>And in accordance to health and safety protocols in place due to the coronavirus, the social media star wore a black protective mask while in the vicinity of any people.</p>

<p>Sporty: The TikTok star, 19, showed off her curves in black leggings and a matching sports bra</p>

<p>On the go: Rae (born Addison Rae Easterling) appeared to head out of the gym with a couple of friends by her side</p>

<p>Rae (born Addison Rae Easterling) appeared to head out of the gym with a couple of friends by her side. Eventually the three said their goodbyes and went their separate ways.  </p>

<p>Addison is headed to the silver screen as one of the leads in a new version of She's All That, that's been renamed He's All That. </p>

<p>The original teen romantic comedy starred Freddie Prinze Jr. and Rachael Leigh Cook </p>

<p>Massive: The Louisiana native has become a major TikTok influencer since joining in July 2019</p>

<p>Rae joined TikTok in July 2019, and proceeded to upload dance videos to trending songs on her the platform. By the end of October 2019, she topped over one million followers, which, in hindsight, became a major milestone mark.</p>

<p>'I remember that's when it changed for me,' the teenager told Business Insider in April 2020. </p>

<p>'I knew I wanted to take it more seriously and expand it to other platforms. I uploaded a video to YouTube and got really active on Instagram.</p>

<p>Her popular dances have since caught the attention of such celebrities as Mariah Carey and Kourtney Kardashian, who has since forged a friendship with the budding multi-media star.                    </p>

<p>Big bucks: Addison Rae was named the highest-earning TikTok personality in Forbes' first-ever list, raking in over $5 million in one calendar year ending in June 2020</p>
